name: r-dtplyr
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.2.1" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-dtplyr
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/dtplyr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/dtplyr/dtplyr_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 2640e9cde4eaa06f02cff29e3f2b99fdd08488df07ea2e6629b2ed6a8285d0f3

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-crayon
    - r-data.table >=1.12.4
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.1
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyselect

  run:
    - r-base
    - r-crayon
    - r-data.table >=1.12.4
    - r-dplyr >=0.8.1
    - r-rlang
    - r-tibble
    - r-tidyselect

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('dtplyr')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('dtplyr')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/hadley/dtplyr
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: This implements the data table back-end for 'dplyr' so that you can seamlessly use data table and 'dplyr' together.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - philip-khor
